      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what's wrong and is it safe to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That loud humming noise is a classic sign of a stuck fan motor, often caused by a seized bearing or a capacitor that has lost its charge. It's definitely not safe to go look at it right now, especially if the unit is hot or if there's a risk of electrical shock; you should turn off the breaker first and let it cool down before investigating.\n\nYou can try checking the safety switch on the outdoor unit, but if the fan still won't spin, you'll likely need to call a professional technician. A DIY repair here is risky because the fan motor is heavy and under tension, and if you try to force it, you could end up with a broken shaft or a snapped belt that makes the situation worse.\n\nJust remember, even if you're not a fan of working with electricity, the best approach is to let the experts handle it. If you do decide to investigate, wear protective gear and be prepared for a lot of grease and dust. If you're feeling brave, you could try checking the capacitor, but if you're not sure, it's better to leave it to the pros.\n\nIf you're feeling adventurous, you could try checking the capacitor, but if you're not sure, it's better to",
